1.title: Arizona Bulls and Blizzards

episode of.title: Fresh Tracks with Randy Newberg (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: This episode shows the adventures of Arizona's late season elk hunts, featuring an Arizona blizzard. Randy and his son, Matthew, are looking for bull elk in the promised land of elk hunting.

4.title: Round 3; New Mexico Elk Rematch

episode of.title: Fresh Tracks with Randy Newberg (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: Randy returns to his favorite New Mexico grasslands to spot and stalk archery bulls. An old elk friend, "One-beam," again becomes the bull of choice in Randy's hunt. Three years prior, the bull was granted a reprieve, in hopes his other antler would re-grow. At 28 yards, "One-beam" and Randy have a 15-minute showdown.

5.title: New Mexico Pronghorn Challenge

episode of.title: Fresh Tracks with Randy Newberg (TV Series 2013– )

5.plot: Randy Newberg shows that pronghorn are his favorite, both to hunt and to eat. This episode has Randy on one of his toughest pronghorn hunts. Good friend Mike Spitzer is along for extra eyes.

6.title: Montana Mule Deer Surprise

episode of.title: Fresh Tracks with Randy Newberg (TV Series 2013– )

6.plot: This episode is about taking advantage of the opportunities that present themselves. In this case, a Montana public land elk hunt turns into an unexpected mule deer bonus.

imdb.plot outline: Leupold's Fresh Tracks with Randy Newberg takes viewers along with America's most dedicated public land hunter. On public lands, weather seldom cooperates and often times the animals win. Always a story to be told; man versus himself, wildlife conservation, public land advocacy, all through the eyes of a hunter who is deeply connected to these lands and the animals he shares them with.
